Chicken and Cauliflower in Garam Masal Tomato Sauce
  --Cook's Country

1 tbsp garam masala
3/4 tsp table salt
1/2 tsp pepper
4 (6-8 oz) boneless, skinless chicken breasts, trimmed and cut into 1-inch pieces
2 tbsp vegetable oil, divided
1/2 head cauliflower (1 lb), cored and cut into 1‚ÅÑ2" florets
1 onion, chopped fine
2 tbsp grated fresh ginger
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 (28 oz) can crushed tomatoes
1/4 c heavy cream

Combine garam masala, salt, and pepper in small bowl. Toss chicken, 1 tbsp oil, and 1 tbsp spice mixture together in medium bowl. Heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in Dutch oven over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add cauliflower and onion and cook until onion is softened, ~5 min. Stir in ginger, garlic, and remaining spice mixture and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Add tomatoes and chicken to pot and bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, until chicken is cooked through and cauliflower is tender, 10-12 min. Off heat, stir in cream. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve over basmati rice.

